1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,040
Who are you here for?

2
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,600
Just think of this place as your own.

3
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:11,280
<i>Who's that woman? She's pretty.</i>

4
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:12,200
She's cute.

5
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,680
Who the hell are you?

6
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:20,080
<i>Don't go to Khao Phrom. Even if you go,</i>

7
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:24,040
<i>it's not like they'll teach you sorcery.</i>

8
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:26,200
You think I don't dare?

9
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:34,080
<i>I've sent my men to hunt him down.</i>
<i>If they can't take him alive, kill him.</i>

10
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:42,560
You want to learn sorcery so badly,
don't you? I'll teach you myself.

11
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:52,360
These bandits. Good they're dead.

12
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:55,040
I heard the governor's men

13
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:58,160
are hunting Bandit Wad right now.

14
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,840
They deserve to be hanged.

15
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,720
May you all find peace in the afterlife.

16
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,680
They will pay for this.

17
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:15,880
Seeing his men hanged like that
must have made Bandit Wad's blood boil.

18
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:19,520
His son Lasor will be next.

19
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,080
When you strike a snake
and fail to break its back,

20
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,520
it always comes back to bite you later.

21
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,960
Be careful, sir.

22
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:31,000
Wad is furious. He will retaliate.

23
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:36,160
If he storms in
like his son did last time, what then?

24
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:39,880
I'll have my nephew Pae and my pirate men

25
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:42,080
guard you personally.

26
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:45,200
Judging by things, Khun Phaeng's men

27
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,440
aren't worth much anyway.

28
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:49,840
Pud,

29
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:52,360
you're looking down on me too much.

30
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,320
I'm just stating facts.

31
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,840
You think you're tough, Pud?

32
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,880
Hey! Enough!

33
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:01,040
You eat from the same pot,
yet you tear each other apart?

34
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,880
The men Khun Phaeng sent
have returned, sir.

35
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,120
- Bring them in.
- Yes, sir.

36
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:22,280
Look.

37
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:26,080
Did you catch Lasor?

38
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,520
He got away, sir.

39
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,720
Damn it!

40
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:31,480
Whoa.

41
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:33,840
You're all useless.

42
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:37,680
Worthless trash. You let him escape

43
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,720
and came back beaten?

44
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:43,600
No, sir. A flock of crows
came and helped him.

45
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:46,080
Look at yourselves.

46
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,080
Open your damn eyes.

47
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,240
Your men couldn't even beat crows.

48
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,520
What are you staring at?

49
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,800
Get out!

50
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,240
You should've used the Saming spell
to cloud the governor's mind

51
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:07,960
and replace Tim as his confidant.

52
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:11,920
Pae, my spell only works temporarily.

53
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,480
Once the incense burns out,
they regain awareness,

54
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:17,000
just like when I enchanted Lasor.

55
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,000
Speaking of Lasor,

56
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:23,240
it must've been the master of Khao Phrom
who sent those crows.

57
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,240
I doubt it.

58
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,880
Old Master Khrua Phut

59
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:30,480
has withdrawn from worldly affairs.
Why would he help a bandit like Lasor?

60
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,600
Then who saved him, Uncle?

61
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,800
Whoever it was doesn't matter.
Tonight, guard the governor well.

62
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,240
Wad won't stay idle.

63
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,120
"This medicine is called Samitthasawaha."

64
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:49,840
"It's made from stalagmite, jade,

65
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:54,160
throne rock, conch shell, Thanum soil,

66
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,000
the nine medicinal cores,
and five lotus flowers,

67
00:05:57,080 --> 00:06:01,040
ground, dissolved in floral water,
and mixed with rock sugar."

68
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,280
"It's highly effective
against curses, venom,

69
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:07,400
and dark rituals
of both humans and demons."

70
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:12,720
A remedy against black magic?

71
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,960
A spell to ward off spirits?

72
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,480
There are spells like this too?

73
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,040
A SPELL TO WARD OFF SPIRITS

74
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,240
TANANG LENANG SAPPAPANINANG LENANG TANANG

75
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:51,520
There are many things in this world
you have yet to know or see.

76
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,760
Study diligently. One day,

77
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:02,240
you will need this knowledge
to help others.

78
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:06,000
But I want to study sorcery more.

79
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:08,920
You still won't abandon the idea
of going back for revenge?

80
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:14,040
My suffering will only end

81
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:17,560
when they face
the consequences of their karma.

82
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,160
Follow me.

83
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,840
Why have you brought me to this cemetery?

84
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:45,760
To abandon desire,

85
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:50,760
one must cultivate kindness
to cleanse hatred.

86
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,360
Human life is short.

87
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:13,840
Do not let hatred cloud your heart.

88
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,920
Let go of vengeance.

89
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:21,320
Erase anger. Forgive.

90
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:25,560
If you can do so,
life will become lighter.

91
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:37,400
These corpses are your teachers.

92
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,120
Contemplate them carefully.

93
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,200
What are you thinking about?

94
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,280
I'm worried about my brother.

95
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:15,360
We've never been apart since childhood.

96
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:26,440
Men always find a way to survive.
It's women like us who suffer more.

97
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,640
If I had been born a man,
it would've been easier.

98
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:40,120
Dad and Uncle Niem
wouldn't have to worry about me like this.

99
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:43,160
And you wouldn't have to hide
your knife-throwing skills.

100
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:47,040
Forcing me to embroider like you?

101
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,240
I'd rather die.

102
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,320
I wish I were strong like you.

103
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:58,560
Don't be strong like me.
Uncle Chaem would just get headaches.

104
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,840
Be strong in your own way. That's enough.

105
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,080
Nui.

106
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,200
Hey.

107
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:10,320
Thank you for healing me.

108
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,480
It's you…

109
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:24,400
Please tell me. Who are you really?

110
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,680
Who I am doesn't matter.

111
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:33,360
Just remember this.

112
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:37,280
I am your benefactor.

113
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,120
I've heard of

114
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:46,600
sacred spirits called "Tuat,"

115
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:50,560
half-beast, half-deity.

116
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:53,720
Tuat Tiger, Tuat Elephant,

117
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,920
Tuat Serpent, Tuat Crocodile.

118
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,800
They bring fortune or doom.

119
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:01,280
Are you…

120
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,880
Tuat Black Crow?

121
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:16,880
Call me whatever you like.

122
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,520
I helped you

123
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:24,440
because you are the one I chose.

124
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,120
You chose me?

125
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:36,080
That's right.

126
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,200
Lasor,

127
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:48,080
I chose you as my disciple.

128
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,480
Thank you, Tuat Black Crow.

129
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:03,440
Lasor, help me.

130
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:05,840
Nui.

131
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:07,880
Nui.

132
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,280
Tuat Black Crow,

133
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,640
my brother was shot. He's badly hurt.

134
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,840
Please save him.

135
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,600
I cannot help him.

136
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,720
Why? You saved me.

137
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,080
His fate

138
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,240
is nearly spent.

139
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,360
His destiny has been severed.

140
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:05,040
Where did they go?

141
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,200
A ghost!

142
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:58,600
Dad, why do we pour water
after making merit?

143
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:01,840
<i>So we can dedicate it</i>
<i>to those we wish to make merit for,</i>

144
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:04,840
or to our karmic creditors.

145
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,560
Will they really receive it?

146
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:09,680
They will.

147
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,840
If the mind is firmly set in compassion,

148
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:15,920
then merit can reach them.

149
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:44,560
Any merit I have ever made…

150
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,520
I dedicate it to you.

151
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:50,800
May you

152
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:53,320
be happy.

153
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,040
May you be free from suffering.

154
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:58,880
May we never harm one another.

155
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,800
Help me!

156
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,000
- Help me!
- Hey!

157
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:06,040
You bastard. You killed my brothers.

158
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:09,359
You framed me and my son for killing Yod.

159
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,480
You don't deserve to live.

160
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,440
Wad,

161
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:39,640
have you forgotten
the Narai shapeshift spell already?

162
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:44,720
You're damn cunning.

163
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:48,680
Killing a weak woman like that,

164
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:52,320
which rule of Khao Phrom did you break?

165
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:56,760
Your magic is weakening, Wad.

166
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,360
Die.

167
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:10,000
Wad, are you wondering

168
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:12,280
why you can't shoot me?

169
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,600
Yod's yantra?

170
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:27,200
You bastard. Did you kill Yod?

171
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:30,800
He's not my father. Why can't I kill him?

172
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:33,880
You damned bastard! Die!

173
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:37,120
<i>Ete-sang sappha-yakkha…</i>

174
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:12,160
How is it? Black-dog-in-heat's blood.

175
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:14,520
I saved a special batch just for you.

176
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:17,880
From a sorcery king bandit,

177
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,080
you're nothing now but a mangy mutt.

178
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:43,520
Send our men out to hunt Bandit Wad down.

179
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:46,840
If you don't bring him back,
don't come back.

180
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,760
Yes, sir.

181
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:51,800
Wad was shot half-dead.
His sorcery has already collapsed.

182
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:55,200
He can't have gone far.
I'll send my men to help search.

183
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,720
Pathetic, both of you.

184
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,000
What kind of guard is this,

185
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:01,560
letting Bandit Wad reach Father's bedroom?

186
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,840
If I hadn't saved your father,

187
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,440
he'd be dead by now.

188
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,760
Arrogant!

189
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:10,160
How dare you talk back to me,
you filthy bandit.

190
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:11,800
Duen.

191
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:17,040
Alright, enough. As long as no one's hurt.

192
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:22,840
But I won't sleep easy
until we catch that father and son.

193
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,480
Who knows when they'll come back again?

194
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,480
Especially Lasor.

195
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:32,200
I want to kill him with my own hands.

196
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,080
We'll capture them alive, sir.

197
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,440
If you can't take them alive,
then kill them.

198
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:42,880
But I want their heads

199
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:44,960
hung at the front of this residence.

200
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:53,160
Honestly, I never trusted them.

201
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:55,880
You mean Khun Paeng or Bandit Pud?

202
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:59,640
Both of them.
Their eyes are scheming and deceitful.

203
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:02,640
Like they've got seven sickles
and seven needles in their bellies.

204
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,960
But they work for Father.

205
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:07,000
Because they benefit from it.

206
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:11,680
I don't want to stay here anymore.
I want to go back to the capital.

207
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:15,840
You want to go back because of them
or because Yiam is gone?

208
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:20,680
Don't pry into my business.
Worry about saving yourself.

209
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,960
I'm not dying that easily.

210
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,000
Nui,

211
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:42,640
how are you?

212
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,240
Lasor…

213
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,280
It hurts.

214
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,360
Hey.

215
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:55,080
Hang in there, Nui.

216
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,960
Get up slowly.

217
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,120
Wait here.

218
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:15,840
I'll go find herbs to treat you.

219
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,800
Lasor.

220
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,360
It's no use.

221
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,480
I know what's coming.

222
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:32,640
You told me

223
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:36,720
you'd never leave me.

224
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:42,960
Even if I die,

225
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:46,520
I'll be a ghost right beside you.

226
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:49,720
I won't let you die.

227
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:51,440
Lasor…

228
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,880
Go back to Father Wad.

229
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:03,840
I've come too far, Nui.

230
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:08,240
Too far to turn back now.

231
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:11,160
Believe me.

232
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:16,240
It's not too late to start over.

233
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:19,600
Father Wad will forgive you.

234
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:23,920
Rest, Nui.

235
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,880
I'll stay right here. I'm not leaving you.

236
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:54,520
This is called a wig.
It's made from real human hair,

237
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:56,800
sewn onto netting.

238
00:24:57,600 --> 00:25:01,840
I saw nobles in the palace
wear them for performances,

239
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,040
so I learned how to make one.

240
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,000
Put it on.

241
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:08,200
You want me to wear a wig?

242
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,160
Yes.

243
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:11,280
Put it on and you'll look like a man.

244
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,760
They won't suspect you.

245
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:17,880
You're going to have Yiwha
disguise herself as a man?

246
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,120
Yes.

247
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:22,840
Yeah.
Since she wants to be a man so badly,

248
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:24,600
let her be one, once and for all.

249
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:27,400
But you need to change clothes too.

250
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:30,120
Wear something like Chang's.
You'll look more convincing.

251
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:34,320
If I were a man, what would I be like?

252
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:38,320
Saeng and his men are coming.

253
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,640
If you're going to do anything, do it now.

254
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:57,880
I'm looking for a prisoner. Pretty face.
Good at throwing knives.

255
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:00,800
About this tall. Have you seen her?

256
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:07,440
- Search the whole place.
- Yes.

257
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:17,400
You know the penalty for hiding a fugitive

258
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,640
in your home, right?

259
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:22,360
If you don't want your backs whipped raw,
hand her over.

260
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:25,560
I haven't seen her.

261
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:28,840
How could I hand her over?

262
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,520
Saeng, we only found these two.

263
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:49,560
I know Noree.

264
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,800
Who is he?

265
00:26:57,840 --> 00:27:01,000
My nephew. He just arrived from Phuket.

266
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:16,640
What's your name?

267
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:18,000
His name is--

268
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:20,760
I'm asking him, not you, Chang.

269
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:23,840
So?

270
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:28,200
Yak. My name's Yak.

271
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,840
You're the size of an ant,
and you call yourself Yak.

272
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:34,800
When he was born, the umbilical cord
wrapped around his neck.

273
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:36,760
His father named him that
to break the bad luck.

274
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:42,880
While you're here, don't get cocky.

275
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:46,720
Yes. I won't.

276
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:51,720
Search the other houses.

277
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:15,880
I apologize, Uncle Niem, Uncle Chaem.

278
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:19,080
Because of my stubborn arrogance,

279
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,440
I almost dragged everyone into trouble.

280
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:24,040
Saeng's like a rabid dog.

281
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:28,040
Once he's got beef with you,
he won't let go.

282
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:33,480
Whatever you do, think it through.

283
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:36,680
I promised your father
I'd protect you with my life.

284
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:38,800
I don't want to break my word.

285
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:43,400
Yes. I'll be more careful from now on.

286
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:48,280
It's actually good you dress like a man.

287
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,560
Right, Pun?

288
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,480
Mm…

289
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:57,760
But I like you better
when you dress like a normal woman.

290
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,040
How about Noree? Is she cute?

291
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,840
Yes, she's cute.

292
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:15,080
Noree, Pun just complimented you.

293
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,960
If you saw me like this,

294
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:50,440
would you still recognize me, Blur?

295
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:55,880
You like beads?

296
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,320
Next time, I'll buy you some.

297
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:07,560
No need. I like this bracelet

298
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,760
because the person I love gave it to me.

299
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:16,320
You already have someone you love, Yiwha?

300
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:21,440
But I don't know
when we'll see each other again.

301
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:24,800
You must love him very much.

302
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:32,320
I do. He's my first love.

303
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:37,720
No wonder.

304
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:42,080
You never look at me.

305
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:48,640
Pun,

306
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,600
even if I can't love you,

307
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:55,720
I can still be your friend.

308
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:20,840
Tell me.

309
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:22,560
Among these herbs,

310
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:26,000
which are beneficial,

311
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:27,760
and which are harmful?

312
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:40,040
I can't answer that, Master.

313
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,680
Why not?

314
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,520
Every herb carries both benefit and harm.

315
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:51,760
Even Siam weed can stop bleeding,

316
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:54,880
but if eaten, it becomes poison.

317
00:31:55,480 --> 00:32:00,200
That's why I can't divide them
into good and bad.

318
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:02,560
Every herb,

319
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:04,760
no matter how beneficial,

320
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:07,600
also holds danger.

321
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,720
Just like sorcery.

322
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:13,440
It can be used for good or for evil.

323
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:19,840
Master, what I encountered last night…

324
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:24,840
Kindness has the power to protect.

325
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:29,280
It lets one sleep in peace, wake in peace,

326
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:32,920
and be loved by humans and spirits alike.

327
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:35,320
A mind filled with kindness

328
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:37,800
is calm,

329
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:41,200
freed from the snare
of hatred and vengeance.

330
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:46,920
You won't teach me sorcery

331
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:51,440
as long as I still cling
to vengeance in my heart.

332
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:58,840
Answer me.

333
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:02,280
Besides revenge,

334
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:05,160
what do you want to learn sorcery for?

335
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:32,160
<i>Evamme sutang ekang samayang</i>

336
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:34,600
<i>Bhagava rajagahe</i>

337
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:40,480
<i>Viharati gicchakute pabbate</i>
<i>atha kho cattaro maharacha…</i>

338
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:26,679
<i>Om, crow. Om, Durga.</i>

339
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,960
<i>Om, Kawi.</i>

340
00:34:30,239 --> 00:34:34,560
<i>All sacred beings, all gods and angels,</i>
<i>descend upon this place.</i>

341
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,120
Lasor.

342
00:34:50,239 --> 00:34:51,320
Come to me.

343
00:34:56,520 --> 00:34:57,960
Tonight is the auspicious night
of the new moon.

344
00:34:58,040 --> 00:35:00,360
I will perform the rite
to accept you as my disciple.

345
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,200
Really, Tuat Black Crow?

346
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:05,000
Yes. Really.

347
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:09,560
I will make you greater than your father.

348
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:13,600
Your father will be proud
to call you his son, Lasor.

349
00:35:17,640 --> 00:35:20,280
I'm ready to learn from you, Master.

350
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:21,760
But I am not ready yet.

351
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:25,360
I need something for my offering.

352
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:27,160
What is it?

353
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,000
His life.

354
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:42,400
I can't. He's my brother.

355
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:44,040
I can't give him to you.

356
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:49,920
Lasor, he won't survive anyway.

357
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:55,680
Slit his throat. Offer his blood to
the Goddess, and you will be my disciple.

358
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:01,800
Lasor…

359
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:05,120
Lasor,

360
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:06,680
I'm scared…

361
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:08,960
Look at his wound.

362
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,200
Nui,

363
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,960
don't be scared.

364
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,880
I would never kill you. I swear.

365
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:21,840
Lasor,

366
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,280
it hurts so much…

367
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:27,520
Kill me.

368
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,680
Kill me.

369
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,360
Nui.

370
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,520
You'll let him suffer like this?

371
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:40,080
I won't make it anyway.

372
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:43,360
Kill me, so you can learn sorcery.

373
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:45,280
Sorcery is waiting for you.

374
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:47,120
No.

375
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:50,120
You're my brother.

376
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:52,960
Kill him.

377
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,280
Kill me,

378
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,360
so I can be free from this pain.

379
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:03,000
Do it. Set him free.

380
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:05,080
You have to do it.

381
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:17,720
Do it. Do it.

382
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:28,640
No!

383
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:35,960
I can't do it.

384
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:38,480
I won't learn it anymore.

385
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:42,440
If you won't kill him, then don't.
I won't wait for you.

386
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,480
Wait!

387
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:23,200
I'm sorry.

388
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:41,040
This sacred rite is complete.

389
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:43,320
Lasor,

390
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:48,080
from this moment on, you are my disciple.

391
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:52,160
When your heart is ready,

392
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:54,880
I will come and teach you.

393
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:21,360
<i>Answer me. Besides revenge,</i>

394
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:24,840
<i>what do you want to learn sorcery for?</i>

395
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,120
<i>Blur.</i>

396
00:39:30,680 --> 00:39:31,520
Orror.

397
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:46,720
Blur.

398
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:57,840
Do you miss me?

399
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:02,800
How did you get here?

400
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:12,600
You…

401
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:19,360
Let's do something fun together.

402
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,200
A spirit?

403
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:10,440
A spell to ward off spirits?

404
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:11,960
A SPELL TO WARD OFF SPIRITS

405
00:41:12,040 --> 00:41:13,640
TANANG LENANG SAPPAPANINANG LENANG TANANG

406
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:17,840
<i>Lenang</i>

407
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:21,080
<i>tanang sappapaninang…</i>

408
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,880
Besides revenge,

409
00:41:46,960 --> 00:41:49,680
what do you want to learn sorcery for?

410
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:57,120
I want to learn sorcery to protect myself

411
00:41:57,640 --> 00:42:01,440
and to help others survive
the evil power that seeks to control us.

412
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,040
Forgive me, Nui.

413
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:24,760
I won't let you die for nothing.

414
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:34,920
Lasor.

415
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:39,320
Are you ready

416
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:41,400
to learn from me now?

417
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:52,320
I'm ready.

418
00:43:17,880 --> 00:43:21,360
YANTANG SANTANG PATANG APHISAMEJJA

419
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:47,680
You still have a long road ahead, Lasor.

420
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:36,160
Good.

421
00:47:12,440 --> 00:47:15,480
TITLE DEED

422
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:23,280
Aiya! Why is it so expensive?

423
00:47:23,360 --> 00:47:24,360
ONE YEAR LATER

424
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:25,760
Whoa…

425
00:47:26,440 --> 00:47:28,080
Everything's expensive.

426
00:47:28,160 --> 00:47:31,160
Why are you complaining
first thing in the morning, Pa?

427
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:34,360
Prices

428
00:47:34,440 --> 00:47:36,120
are skyrocketing these days.

429
00:47:36,200 --> 00:47:38,560
At this rate, the villagers will starve.

430
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:40,360
What kind of police are you?

431
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:44,000
Why don't you arrest the hoarders?

432
00:47:44,080 --> 00:47:44,960
Huh?

433
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:50,000
Tycoon Thongyoo's behind it.

434
00:47:50,680 --> 00:47:52,200
He's in on it with the governor.

435
00:47:53,040 --> 00:47:54,360
Who would dare touch him?

436
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:56,320
And Tim

437
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:59,440
sends men to extort villagers every day.

438
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:02,640
Bandit Pud's gang
keeps robbing people nonstop.

439
00:48:02,720 --> 00:48:04,920
I arrest them,
they're released the next day.

440
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:06,320
Seriously.

441
00:48:08,040 --> 00:48:11,080
This world is sinking into chaos.

442
00:48:11,160 --> 00:48:14,160
At this rate,
this town will become a den of bandits.

443
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:16,560
Not good.

444
00:48:21,080 --> 00:48:22,160
Are you here to buy something?

445
00:48:22,760 --> 00:48:26,160
- Rice and sugar.
- You're not going to the station?

446
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:27,520
I'm off duty already.

447
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:30,160
I'll get it for you.

448
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:34,000
- Pun.
- Yes?

449
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:35,880
Don't give them too much extra.

450
00:48:35,960 --> 00:48:38,000
I'll go bankrupt.

451
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:39,400
I know, Pa.

452
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:49,160
- Chin Seng.
- Yes?

453
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:50,800
Please get everything on this list for me.

454
00:48:53,480 --> 00:48:54,640
Oh.

455
00:48:54,720 --> 00:48:57,600
What are you buying all this for?

456
00:48:57,680 --> 00:48:59,800
It's hard to make a living here now,

457
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:03,240
so I'm taking goods to sell elsewhere.

458
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:07,040
And I plan to offer supplies
to Old Master Khrua Phut at Khao Phrom.

459
00:49:08,840 --> 00:49:12,160
Good, good. I rejoice in your merit.

460
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:14,440
I'll pack it. Wait a moment.

461
00:49:15,680 --> 00:49:18,680
Brother, you're going to Khao Phrom?

462
00:49:23,600 --> 00:49:26,840
- I want to go there too.
- Why?

463
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:30,800
My brother once dreamed
of learning sorcery.

464
00:49:30,880 --> 00:49:32,920
Maybe he's there.

465
00:49:34,960 --> 00:49:37,480
Khao Phrom is deep in the wilderness.

466
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:40,160
You must travel day and night.

467
00:49:40,240 --> 00:49:42,640
You're a woman.
It won't be easy. Don't go.

468
00:49:42,720 --> 00:49:45,040
Yes. The forest is dangerous,

469
00:49:45,120 --> 00:49:48,000
bandits, wild beasts, jungle fever.
Don't risk it.

470
00:49:48,960 --> 00:49:52,000
It's been a year.
I haven't heard anything about my brother.

471
00:49:52,080 --> 00:49:54,320
I don't know if he's alive or dead.

472
00:49:56,560 --> 00:49:59,280
If he completes his training,
he'll come back to you himself.

473
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:31,120
You killed my family.

474
00:50:32,400 --> 00:50:33,880
I killed your family.

475
00:50:35,880 --> 00:50:37,120
And finally,

476
00:50:38,240 --> 00:50:39,680
we met.

477
00:50:40,520 --> 00:50:42,200
Today is the day you die.

478
00:50:45,360 --> 00:50:46,480
If you have something,

479
00:50:47,080 --> 00:50:48,120
show me.

480
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:50,520
You!

481
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:53,320
Hey.

482
00:51:38,840 --> 00:51:39,760
Come on!

483
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:02,640
Kill me.

484
00:52:05,360 --> 00:52:06,560
I will kill you.

485
00:52:10,280 --> 00:52:11,840
Go to hell.

486
00:52:18,200 --> 00:52:20,000
<i>Answer me.</i>

487
00:52:20,080 --> 00:52:21,720
<i>Besides revenge,</i>

488
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:24,240
<i>what do you want to learn sorcery for?</i>

489
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:26,840
I want to learn sorcery to protect myself

490
00:52:27,560 --> 00:52:31,040
and to help others survive
the evil power that seeks to control us.

491
00:53:08,480 --> 00:53:09,560
Yiwha is gone?

492
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:13,640
Yes. Since we came back from the market,
no one's seen her.

493
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:14,800
Her clothes are gone too.

494
00:53:15,320 --> 00:53:17,400
She's a woman. Where could she have gone?

495
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:23,200
Or is she going to Khao Phrom?

496
00:53:23,920 --> 00:53:25,040
Why would she go there?

497
00:53:25,640 --> 00:53:27,720
Yiwha said she's going to
look for her brother.

498
00:53:28,520 --> 00:53:31,160
Damn it. That's asking for trouble.

499
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:34,440
So what do we do now, Uncle?

500
00:53:34,520 --> 00:53:37,280
We go after her.
Bring Yiwha back no matter what.

501
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:40,360
I'll ask my fellow officers
to search around Khao Phrom.

502
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:41,840
I'm going too.

503
00:53:41,920 --> 00:53:44,240
Let's go.

504
00:54:11,080 --> 00:54:12,640
I'm sorry, Uncle Niem.

505
00:54:13,640 --> 00:54:16,400
I just want to see Lasor once.

506
00:54:39,520 --> 00:54:41,000
I've come to bid you farewell, Master.

507
00:54:41,560 --> 00:54:43,360
Use what you've learned

508
00:54:43,440 --> 00:54:47,120
to benefit yourself and help others

509
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,360
escape ignorance.

510
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:51,920
Safe travels, Yiam.

511
00:55:44,440 --> 00:55:46,920
So this is Khao Phrom…

512
00:56:07,440 --> 00:56:08,480
Blur…

513
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:16,880
Orror…

514
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:55,240
<i>Remember, my blood</i>

515
00:56:55,320 --> 00:56:56,200
<i>runs in your veins.</i>

516
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:59,960
<i>You have completed</i>
<i>your sorcery under me, Lasor.</i>

517
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:06,040
Wad!

518
00:57:08,240 --> 00:57:10,880
<i>Pathavi-dhatu dighangva</i>

519
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:12,440
<i>pakasaja jiva</i>

520
00:57:12,520 --> 00:57:13,480
<i>utehi.</i>

521
00:57:14,560 --> 00:57:15,840
From now on,

522
00:57:16,360 --> 00:57:18,160
you will be with me forever.

523
00:57:18,760 --> 00:57:20,160
You still haven't told me

524
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:22,040
what you're going to do
in the Banthat Mountain Range.

525
00:57:22,120 --> 00:57:24,840
<i>I must go there to search for something.</i>

526
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:27,040
What is it? Tell me.

527
00:57:27,120 --> 00:57:28,800
It is Klaikot Lek Lai.

528
00:57:29,640 --> 00:57:33,160
<i>The supreme form of Lek Lai.</i>
<i>Whoever possesses Klaikot Lek Lai</i>

529
00:57:33,240 --> 00:57:34,760
<i>will be invincible.</i>

530
00:58:18,320 --> 00:58:21,880
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
